<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,484,1258]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,559,585]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[441,513,560,586]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="8.[151,269,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,196,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[218,1369,194,1898]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Adults of Scrobipalpa spp. 1, S. fusca sp. n. (HT); 2, S. latiuncella sp. n. (HT); 3, S. flavimaculata sp. n. (HT); 4, S. sattleri (Lvovsky &amp; Piskunov) 5, S. divergens Povolný (HT); 6, S. erichiodes sp. n. (HT); 7, S. nigrigrisea sp. n. (PT); 8, S. distincta sp. n. (HT)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196089/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[496,513,560,586]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
): Wingspan 13.0 mm. Head and thorax white. Labial palpus white, segment 
<number box="[1421,1436,560,586]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
with rare light brown scales. Tegula light yellow. Scape white, other antennal segments light brown with broad basal white rings. Forewing yellowish-white, with two diffused yellow spots at base of cell and prolonged yellow spot at corner of cell; brown scales along costal margin. Hindwing light grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,484,1258]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[394,488,709,735]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 24" captionStartId="10.[151,270,1865,1889]" captionTargetBox="[217,1389,194,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[186,1401,194,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 24. Male genitalia of Scrobipalpa spp. 17, S. fusca sp. n. (PT, slide no. 222 / 07); 18, S. latiuncella sp. n. (HT, slide no. 277 / 08); 19, S. flavimaculata sp. n. (HT, slide no. SYW 05309); 20, S. sattleri Lvovsky &amp; Piskunov (slide no. SYW 05192); 21, S. divergens Povolný (HT, slide no. 210 / 07); 22, S. erichiodes sp. n. (PT, slide no. 101 / 08); 23, S. erichiodes sp. n. (PT, slide no. 74 / 08); 24, S. nigrigrisea sp. n. (HT, slide no. 88 / 08)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196091/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[453,488,709,735]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
): Uncus sub-rectangular, slightly longer than broad; apex with small medial incision. Gnathos small, sickle-shaped. Tegumen comparatively broad. Valva slender, widened distally, far exceeding top of uncus. Sacculus digitate, rounded apically, with small acute tip; about one-quarter length of valva. Paired processes on posterior margin of vinculum basally broad, narrowed to distinctly rounded and outwards curved tip distally, slightly shorter than sacculus. Saccus very short and slender. Aedeagus weakly flattened at base, sub-oval; distal part straight, with distinct apical cornutus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,484,1258]" box="[197,422,933,959]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Female: Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,484,1258]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,328,970,996]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Povolny, 1977" authorityName="Povolny" authorityYear="1977" box="[682,958,970,996]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis box="[682,773,970,995]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">S. lutea</emphasis>
Povolný, 
<number box="[898,958,970,996]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</taxonomicName>
superficially, but differs in the broader forewing with yellow rather than grey spots and yellowish-white apex. The male genitalia resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Povolny" authorityName="Povolny" box="[151,417,1045,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candicans">
<emphasis box="[151,304,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">S. candicans</emphasis>
Povolný
</taxonomicName>
, but differ in the distinctly shorter paired processes of vinculum, broader uncus and longer valva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1022,1119,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,484,1258]" box="[197,1022,1119,1146]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,297,1119,1145]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Biology.</emphasis>
