<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,484,1258]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,330,1194,1220]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[860,930,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">flavus</emphasis>
– yellow, 
<emphasis box="[1050,1171,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">maculatus</emphasis>
– spot, referring to the yellow spots on forewing.
</paragraph>
